>A long, long time ago I wrote a driver that would allow you to 
>control individual bits on the parport. You're welcome to port
>it a reasonably recent kernel. 
Oh, incidentally, recent 2.3 kernels include "ppdev" which allows you to 
twiddle with the parallel port registers from user space in a relatively clean 
fashion.  It doesn't give you bit addressing for the output lines but it would 
be somewhat easy to add this on top.
